<Speech Act Extractor Summary>
- Purpose: extract one or more speech acts from an utterance.
- Output format: valid JSON with one key, speech acts (array).

Core rules:
- Parse utterance into minimal actionable units that modify chart/data state.
- Return JSON-only output with no extra commentary.
- Preserve extracted actions as concise phrases suitable for downstream task inference.

Public-release note:
- Full prompt examples and detailed edge-case rules are omitted in this public release.
</Speech Act Extractor Summary>
